Point $P$ is randomly selected inside triangle $ABC$.  What is the probability that $P$ is closer to $C$ than it is to either $A$ or $B$?

Below is a partial solution. Please continue solving from where it left off:
Let $\ell$ be the perpendicular bisector of segment $AC$.
We note that the points that are closer to $A$ than they are to $C$ are the points that are on the same side of $\ell$ as $A$.
[asy]
